ssembly of Bihar]]. It is comes under [[Pataliputra (Lok Sabha constituency)|Pataliputra]] lok sabha constituency along with other assembly constituencies viz Masaurhi, Maner, Phulwari, Paliganj and Bikram.<ref>[http://www.travelindia-guide.com/assembly-elections/bihar/constituency-results/danapur.php Danapur Assembly Constituency] December 20, 2013</ref>\n\n==Overview==\nDanapur comprises CD Block [[Danapur]]-Cum-[[Khagaul]].<ref name=commission>{{cite web|url = http://eci.nic.in/eci_main/CurrentElections/CONSOLIDATED_ORDER%20_ECI%20.pdf  |title = Schedule \u2013 XIII of Constituencies Order, 2008 of Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly constituencies Order, 2008 of the Election Commission of India|work= Schedule VI Bihar, Part A \u2013 Assembly constituencies, Part B \u2013 Parliamentary constituencies  |publisher = |accessdate = 2013-12-20 }}</ref>\n[[File:Patna district assembly.png|thumb|center|Danapur in Patna district]]\n\n==Member of Legislative Assembly==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Assembly\n!Duration\n!Name of the Member\n!Political Party\n|-\n| Second||1957-1962  || [[Jagat Narayan Lal]] ||  [[Indian National Congress]]\n|-\n| Third||1962-67|| [[Ram Sewak Singh]] || [[Sanghata Socialist Party]]\n|-\n| Fourth||1967-1969|| [[Ram Sewak Singh]] || [[Sanghata Socialist Party]]\n|-\n| Fifth||1969-1972|| [[Budh Deo Singh]] || [[Indian National Congress]]\n|-\n| Sixth||1972-1977|| [[Budh Deo Singh]] || [[Indian National Congress]]\n|-\n| Seventh||1977-1980|| [[Ram Lakhan Singh Yadav]] || [[Indian National Congress]]\n|-\n| Eighth||1980-1985|| [[Budh Deo Singh]] || [[Indian National Congress (I)]]\n|-\n| Ninth||1985-1990|| [[Vijendra Ray Yadav]] || [[Independent politician|Independent]]\n|-\n| Tenth||1990-1995|| [[Vijendra Ray Yadav]] || [[Janata Dal]]\n|-\n| Eleventh||1995-2000|| [[Vijay Singh Yadav]] || [[Bharatiya Janata Party]]\n|-\n| Twelfth||2000-2005|| [[Lalu Prasad Yadav]]|| [[Rashtriya Janata Dal ]]\n|-\n| Thirteenth||2005-2010|| [[Asha Devi Yada