{"title_page": "Bohemia (rapper)", "text_new": "{{short description|American rapper and producer}}\n{{BLP sources|date=April 2017}}\n{{EngvarB|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Bohemia\n| native_name      = \n| background       = solo_singer\n| image            = \n| birth_name       = Roger David\n| alias            = Raja\n| occupation       = {{flatlist|\n* [[Rapping|Rapper]]\n* [[Record producer]]\n* [[Music director]]\n* [[Musician]]\n* [[Poet]]\n* [[Actor]]\n}}\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1979|10|15}}<ref name=Birthday/>{{better source|reason=Doesn't mention year of birth or age|date=May 2019}}\n| birth_place      = [[Karachi]], [[Sindh, Pakistan]]\n| module           = {{Infobox musical artist \n| embed=yes\n| origin =  [[Oakland]], [[California]], [[United States]]\n| background = solo_singer <!--includes rappers-->\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[Desi hip hop]]\n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[Rap]]\n}}\n| years_active = 2001\u2013present\n| associated_acts =\n| label = {{flatlist|\n* [[Universal Music Group]]\n* [[Sony Music India]]\n* [[Kali Denali Music]]\n* [[Super Cassettes Industries T-Series|T-Series]]\n* [[Yash Raj Films]]\n}}\n| URL = {{URL|thepunjabirapper.com}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Roger David''' (born October 15, 1979), better known by his stage name '''Bohemia''' ({{lang-pa|{{Nastaliq|\u0628\u0648\u06c1\u06cc\u0645\u06cc\u0627}}}}, {{Lang|pa|\u0a2c\u0a4b\u0a39\u0a40\u0a2e\u0a40\u0a06}}, stylised '''BOHEMIA''' or '''Raja'''), is a Pakistani American rapper and record producer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2018/10/02/cricketer-tanvirs-brother-files-law-suit-against-rapper-bohemia/|title=Cricketer Tanvir's brother files law suit against rapper Bohemia {{!}} Pakistan Today|website=www.pakistantoday.com.pk|access-date=May 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://images.dawn.com/news/1180648|title=Pakistani-American rapper Bohemia set to make acting debut|last=Staff|first=Images|date=August 10, 2018|website=Images|language=en|access-date=May 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.pakistantoday.com.pk/2018/01/20/bohemia-dedicates-new-song-gumraah-to-victims-of-abuse/|title=Bohemia dedicates new song Gumraah to victims of abuse {{!}} Pakistan Today|website=www.pakistantoday.com.pk|access-date=May 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/95536/pakistani-rapper-bohemia-in-bollywood-again/|title=Pakistani rapper Bohemia in Bollywood again|last=Tribune.com.pk|date=December 27, 2010|website=The Express Tribune|language=en-US|access-date=May 12, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thestatesman.com/cities/bohemia-perform-live-delhi-friday-1502715820.html|title=Bohemia to perform live in Delhi on Friday|date=December 12, 2018|website=The Statesman|language=en-US|access-date=May 12, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nBohemia was born on October 15, 1979,<ref name=Birthday>{{cite web|url=http://mtv.in.com/thebuzz/music/this-day-in-music/tdim-bohemias-birthday-15th-oct-51075547.html |title=TDIM \u2013 Bohemia's Birthday \u2013 15th Oct |publisher=[[MTV]]|date=October 15, 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150627082400/https://www.mtvindia.com/thebuzz/music/this-day-in-music/tdim-bohemias-birthday-15th-oct-51075547.html|archive-date=June 27, 2014 |accessdate=May 14, 2019}}</ref>{{better source|reason=Doesn't mention year of birth or age|date=May 2019}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.opf.org.pk/prides/bohemia-rapper/|title=Bohemia (rapper)|website=OVERSEAS PAKISTANIS FOUNDATION|language=en-US|access-date=January 10, 2020}}</ref> in [[Karachi]], [[Sindh]] and did his schooling in [[Peshawar]], [[Pakistan]]. At the age of 13, he moved to the United States with his family.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/327622/more-than-just-forties-and-shorties/|title=Bohemia: More than just forties and shorties|last=Mahmood|first=Rafay|date=January 27, 2012|work=The Express Tribune|access-date=August 31, 2018|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nIn early 2000 he moved to join his cousin in [[Oakland]] who was working at a [[West Oakland]] recording studio, and introduced him to a young hip-hop producer called Sha One (Seth Agress). Discovering that they both shared a deep interest in music, they made plans to form their own record label, which they subsequently called \"The Outfit Entertainment\". After Sha heard Bohemia reciting something he had written in Punjabi he asked him to rap it over one of his beats. Over the next few months, he wrote a library of lyrics. This would become the arsenal for his debut album ''Vich Pardesan De (In The Foreign Land)'' \u2013 an autobiographical story of his life as a Desi youngster adopting to the streets of America, which he and Sha One produced together. Their first single \"Sha Te Ra\" was released as a music video, but the song itself was not included on ''Vich Pardesan De''.\n\nThe following album, ''[[Pesa Nasha Pyar]]'' [Money, Intoxication, Love] became the first full-length Punjabi rap album released by a major label. It was recorded and produced by Sha One and Bohemia in their downtown Oakland studio. After nearly two years of perfecting their sound and style, a seamless fusion of Bohemia's Punjabi vocals, and Sha One's English hooks, the album was finally released. He subsequently signed a multi-record deal with music label [[Universal Music Group]]. In 2006, ''Pesa Nasha Pyar'' was on the Top 10 downloads of [[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]], and No. 3 on [[Planet M]] chart India.<ref name=\"selfbio\">{{cite web|url=http://thepunjabirapper.com/bio/ |title=Bio |publisher=Thepunjabirapper.com |author=Bohemia |date=August 30, 2012 |accessdate=July 25, 2014}} {{unreliable source?|date=July 2014}}</ref> His first album Vich Pardesan De get nominated in BBC UK top ten albums. ''[[Da Rap Star]]'', his third album, received four nominations at the [[UK Asian Music Awards]] and [[PTC Punjabi]] music awards. It also remained at No. 1 on [[Planet M]] chart several weeks.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/artists/bohemia/biography/ |title=Bohemia Bio &#124; Bohemia Career |publisher=MTV |date= |accessdate=June 27, 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe performed the title track for [[Warner Bros]] film ''[[Chandni Chowk to China]]'', appearing in the film with [[Akshay Kumar]] and [[Deepika Padukone]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1091229/|title=Chandni Chowk to China (2009)|author=jfsocc|date=January 16, 2009|work=IMDb|accessdate=March 9, 2015}}</ref> A few months later he did the title track for another Akshay Kumar film, ''[[8 x 10 Tasveer]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt1105709/|title=8 x 10 Tasveer (2009)|author=manojharisree|date=April 3, 2009|work=IMDb|accessdate=March 9, 2015}}</ref> In 2011, he gave a song as a present to Akshay Kumar for his first Hollywood production [[Breakaway (2011 film)|''Breakaway'']].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bohemiathepunjabirapper.wordpress.com/2011/09/03/sansaar-breakaway-2011/|title=Sansaar [Breakaway 2011]|work=Bohemia The Punjabi Rapper|accessdate=March 9, 2015|date=September 3, 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2012, [[Sony Music India]] signed Bohemia. As part of the association, Sony Music managed his music albums, launches and shows under its \nmanagement program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-sony-music-signs-punjabi-rapper-bohemia-1695286 |title=Sony Music signs Punjabi rapper Bohemia |work=Daily News & Analysis |publisher=Dnaindia.com |date=May 29, 2012 |accessdate=June 27, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author= |url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2012-05-29/news-and-interviews/31886974_1_sony-music-bohemia-singer-shot |title=Sony Music signs singer Bohemia |work=Times of India |date=May 29, 2012 |accessdate=October 14, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2012 he released his fourth album ''[[Thousand Thoughts]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/thousand-thoughts/id557296420|title=iTunes \u2013 Music \u2013 Thousand Thoughts by Bohemia|work=iTunes|accessdate=March 9, 2015}}</ref> In 2013, it won Best Non-Resident Punjabi Album award at [[PTC Punjabi]] Music Awards.<ref name=\"indiatimes1\">{{cite news| url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-03-25/music/38009229_1_miss-pooja-honey-singh-sudesh-kumari | work=The Times of India | title=PTC Punjabi Music Awards winners  |date=March 25, 2013}}</ref> At the [[Coke Studio (Pakistan)|Coke Studio]] Sessions he was the first rap artist, appearing in their [[Coke Studio Pakistan (season 5)|fifth season]] where he performed three songs. Bohemia has also recorded a collaboration with [[Sonu Kakkar]] and Jamaican American artist [[Sean Kingston]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thepunjabirapper.com/iraj-sean-kingston-2014-01-17/|title=BOHEMIA, IRAJ, SEAN KINGSTON|work=BOHEMIA|accessdate=March 9, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150303052956/http://thepunjabirapper.com/iraj-sean-kingston-2014-01-17/|archivedate=March 3, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Bohemia launched his own music label Kali Denali Music.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thepunjabirapper.com/main-2014-11-07|title=Main|work=BOHEMIA|accessdate=March 9, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150223233509/http://thepunjabirapper.com/main-2014-11-07/|archivedate=February 23, 2015}}</ref> Bohemia appeared in [[XXL (magazine)|''XXL'']] magazine in New York.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\"/>\n\nIn 2017, Bohemia released his latest album ''[[Skull & Bones: The Final Chapter]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Skull & Bones by Bohemia |url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/skull-bones/1203224959 |website=iTunes |accessdate=November 17, 2018 |date=February 13, 2017}}</ref>\n\nOn July 26, 2018, first single \"Sandesa\" from his upcoming album Skull & Bones: Volume 2 was released, which turned out to be a remixed version of one of his unreleased singles. On November 27, 2018, Bohemia released first original single \"Koi Farak Nahi\" for his album ''[[Skull & Bones: Volume 2]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Koi Farak Nahi - Single |url=https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/koi-farak-nahi-single/1444663697 |website=iTunes |accessdate=November 27, 2018 |date=November 27, 2018}}</ref> In an interview Bohemia said that he is coming back with his brand new album ''Skull and Bones Volume 2'' which is scheduled for release in 2019 on his own label, Kali Denali Music, and has many featured artists on it.\n\nAt the end of 2018 Bohemia went on a tour in India, where he performed in Chandigarh, Delhi, Mumbai, and Rajasthan. He also appeared on an Episode on No.1 Yaarian With [[Raftaar (rapper)|Raftaar]] and [[Salim Merchant]].\n\nIn February 2019 Bohemia released the third single \"Umeed\" from the album ''Skull and Bones Volume 2''.\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{awards table}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2010\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\"[[Da Rap Star]]\"\n| Best Punjabi Album at PTC Punjabi Music Awards\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2010\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\"[[Da Rap Star]]\"\n| Best Sound Recording at PTC Punjabi Music Awards\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2010\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\"[[Da Rap Star]]\"\n| Best Punjabi Music Director at PTC Punjabi Music Awards\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2010\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\"[[Da Rap Star]]\"\n| Best International Album at [[UK Asian Music Awards]]\n|{{nom}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2013\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\"[[Thousand Thoughts]]\"\n| Best International Album at PTC Punjabi Music Awards\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|2015\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|\"Excellence Music\"\n| Award of Excellence - Music at [[Festival of Globe|FOG]] Festival Of Globe\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|2015\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| \"Music Career\"